# Performance Standards

Database:
- No N+1 queries — use joinedload() or selectinload() explicitly
- Never fetch unbounded datasets — all list queries must be paginated
- Select explicit columns — avoid SELECT *
- Index foreign keys and all columns used in WHERE or ORDER BY
- Cache expensive read operations — TTL must be defined, never infinite

API:
- p95 response time budget: reads < 500ms, writes < 1000ms
- Avoid redundant API calls — use React Query caching on the frontend

Frontend:
- Lazy-load routes and heavy components
- No API calls inside render — use hooks with React Query
- No unnecessary re-renders — memoize where profiled as needed (not by default)
